{
  "stem": "24397.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and of course, being-- especially being in the Zionist movement, I felt-- I felt the need to be there, rather than being in the British army.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So at some point I made the decision that that's what I want to do.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I went to my youth movement first, because a lot of the youth movements were doing recruiting at the same time.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Well, my youth movement, they only wanted to send me to a kibbutz.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They didn't want me to join the army.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I had to find another youth movement that would allow-- would get me through to the military line.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I did that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was all kind of cloak and dagger stuff the way it worked then.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "You went to a poke little office in London, where somebody would give you a ticket to board a boat train to France and write on the edge of a newspaper something in Hebrew, roll it in a ball, stick it in your pocket, and that was your identity to give to somebody else when you arrive in Paris.",
      "word_count": 59
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And memorize this address, and I was walking up and down Oxford Street memorizing this address.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Then-- and also rehearsing what to say if the-- if the British customs asks you, you know, how come you only got a one-way ticket and all that.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, you know, a lot of this was in my head.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When I went through the customs, they say where are you going?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I said, I'm going on vacation.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Well, have a great time.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It didn't bother him one bit.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And once we got in Paris, in Marseilles, they already-- the porter there knew that we were going to Israel.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was such a usual route.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
